body:
🍂”hey pretty boy”🍂

……………………

Ship: namkook

Author: me :)

Genre: fluff

an au were jeongguk is dragged along to a college party by a few of his friends, only to make a new one.

……………………

“God. I actually hate you.” Jeongguk scoffs as the cold night breeze hits him reminding him that the red denim jacket he was wearing wasn’t exactly the best coat for a night like this. “It will be fun, loosen up gguk.” A low voice replies, causing he younger to roll his eyes. “Shut it, tae. It will not be fun. There’s going to be people, alcohol and people drinking alcohol. I don’t like any of those things.” Despite how serious he was being, Jeongguk was only gifted a chuckle and a shove before he entered the party, the booming music already hurting his ears. Boy was this going to be fun.

You see, Jeongguk didn’t want to be here. Not at all in fact. It was a Friday night and he had just hoped to stay in his dorm and study while listening to music like he usually does, however his room mate and best friend of all time (Taehyung) seemed to have different plans for him. He was just praying there was banana milk on offer.

Just as expected, as soon as he entered the rather large building, all Jeongguk could see were bodies jumping up and down, chatting, laughing and drinking something Jeongguk despised; alcohol. “Here. Keep yourself entertained.” Taehyung yelled over the music while forcing a can of beer into Jeongguk’s hands, causing him to scowl as the older boy ran off. Great.

Determined to the and make the best of things, Jeongguk attempted to make a list of why he should enjoy himself but just came up with a rather pathetic list of why this was going to be a shit night. He was stuck at a party. On his own. No seats were free. He didn’t know the WiFi password. He had no money. He had to drink. And as much as he really wanted to think of tonight as a positive experience, he just really couldn’t. He hated parties. Especially when he was surrounded by sweaty college students. Gross. At least he showers twice a day.

“That’s it…” he mumbled to himself, squeezing in between the tiny gaps between people, some girls ‘aww’ing at him, mainly due to the fact he looked like a little lost lamb rather than a pissed off twenty one year old. After a good amount of time of wandering, he eventually found a stair case which he gladly stumbled up, collapsing with a sigh against the wall. Jeongguk was rather glad to be out of the sweaty disco downstairs but was now burdened with the muffled sounds of girls and boys doing rather 18+ things. At least it was cool up here in comparison to he sqletering temperatures of downstairs.

Jeongguk must have been sat upstairs for a good half an hour before he finally mustered up the courage to take a swig of the beer, a little embarrassed to say he actually enjoyed it and that the remaining liquid inside the can was gone within the next seven minutes. Something about the bitter taste just was so attractive to him, making him a tad bit sleepy too. In fact, Jeongguk found himself even gently fluttering his eyes shut. What a light weight.

However, it wasn’t until the sound of a door opening and foosteps paired with a rather manly smell came toward him that he finally snapped out of his trance, causing his eyes to slowly open, seeing himself still sat against the wall with his knees tucked up to his chest and the empty can of beer laying on the carpet next to him. Did he actually fall asleep?

“Hey pretty boy. Sleepy?” A stranger had asked him, causing Jeongguk to look up, finding the owner of both the voice and the strong smell of boyish cologne. “Hm…?” He hummed, rubbing his eyes lightly. A man with a goofy yet cute smile stood above him, wearing a white shirt, jacket and dark jeans. He had dirty blonde hair which was still rather perfect despite the ovvious fact he had recently been involved with sex (judging by the girl who had just walked out of the room the male had, still struggling to smooth out her skirt). However, there was one thing that Jeongguk couldn’t keep his eyes off ; his dimples. Tiny indents in his cheeks that just made him seem oh so handsome and perfect. It was only then Jeongguk realised that the angel was talking to him yet again, causing him to stutter out an apology.

“I-I’m sorry…I zoned out, what did you say?” He asked, tilting his head causing his rose gold hair to move across his forehead. The man laughed. “No worries bunny. I said I think you’ve had a little too much to drink. You look young, are you sure youre even old enough to be here? You look sixteen. I’m namjoon by the way. Are you here with your older brother or something? Come on, I’m sure we can find him.” ‘Namjoon’ spoke, Jeongguk a little taken back by what he had said. “I’m twenty one, I’m here with my friend.” He began, “Thanks for saying I look young though. Lots of people think that.” Jeongguk stood up, picking up the empty can he had so carelessly left beside him. “I’m just not so used to drinking and got sleepy…I’m Jeongguk.” The younger held out his hand for Namjoon to shake, a little confused when he saw the way his eyes lit up. “You alright?” The shorter male enquires with the raise of a brow, getting a reply of , “Yeah! Sorry, I just don’t get handshakes a lot. I always offer them but they get ignored.”

Unable to resist the urge to giggle, Jeongguk sort of felt sorry for Namjoon, trying to imagine how awkward it must be every time he’s ignored. “That must suck.” He laughed, shoving his hands back into his pockets. The two comintied to talk for a while and ended up laying down on one of the beds in the rooms (after checking for any condoms or cum stains) just to chat and share silly stories to make each other laugh, with different alcoholic beverages that namjoon had provided of course. Due to this, both the boys inevitably ended up completed shit faced, pissing themselves with laughter at things that weren’t even funny. seconds turned into minutes, minutes turned into hours and before ether of them knew it, it was already one am and Jeongguk was being cradled by the taller whom was gently playing with his hair.

“Jeongguk?” A familiar voice could be heard, the younger sitting up only to see Taehyung stood at the door with a worried expression despite the fact he was clearly drunk. “I’ve been calling you for the past twenty minutes, I didn’t know where you were!” He huffed, making his way over to Jeongguk and tugging him off the bed. “Come on, the taxi is here to pick us up.” An audible groan could be heard parting Jeongguk’s lips, causing Namjoon to quickly get up and grab his wrist.

“H-Hey, uh…listen. He can stay for a while longer. I can get him a taxi, he’s fine with me.” Namjoon assured Taehyung who was understandably skeptical at first until Jeongguk looked up at him with a wobbly bottom lip and doe eyes, causing him to huff and let go. “Fine. I want him back by 3am though.” He spoke in a firm voice befor making his way out of the party. The pair were quiet for a minute or so as they stood in the hallway, Namjoon finally breaking the silence.

“Can I have your number?”

………………………..

ew , this is horse shit. sorry it’s not very good, i just decided to try writing out and i hope to get better in the future. send in plots or au’s and i will try them out! any ships.

Just as expected, as soon as he entered the rather large building, all Jeongguk could see were bodies jumping up and down, chatting, laughing and drinking something Jeongguk despised; alcohol. “Here. Keep yourself entertained.” Taehyung yelled over the music while forcing a can of beer into Jeongguk’s hands, causing him to scowl as the older boy ran off. Great.

Determined to the and make the best of things, Jeongguk attempted to make a list of why he should enjoy himself but just came up with a rather pathetic list of why this was going to be a shit night. He was stuck at a party. On his own. No seats were free. He didn’t know the WiFi password. He had no money. He had to drink. And as much as he really wanted to think of tonight as a positive experience, he just really couldn’t. He hated parties. Especially when he was surrounded by sweaty college students. Gross. At least he showers twice a day.

“That’s it…” he mumbled to himself, squeezing in between the tiny gaps between people, some girls ‘aww’ing at him, mainly due to the fact he looked like a little lost lamb rather than a pissed off twenty one year old. After a good amount of time of wandering, he eventually found a stair case which he gladly stumbled up, collapsing with a sigh against the wall. Jeongguk was rather glad to be out of the sweaty disco downstairs but was now burdened with the muffled sounds of girls and boys doing rather 18+ things. At least it was cool up here in comparison to he sqletering temperatures of downstairs.

Jeongguk must have been sat upstairs for a good half an hour before he finally mustered up the courage to take a swig of the beer, a little embarrassed to say he actually enjoyed it and that the remaining liquid inside the can was gone within the next seven minutes. Something about the bitter taste just was so attractive to him, making him a tad bit sleepy too. In fact, Jeongguk found himself even gently fluttering his eyes shut. What a light weight.

However, it wasn’t until the sound of a door opening and foosteps paired with a rather manly smell came toward him that he finally snapped out of his trance, causing his eyes to slowly open, seeing himself still sat against the wall with his knees tucked up to his chest and the empty can of beer laying on the carpet next to him. Did he actually fall asleep?

“Hey pretty boy. Sleepy?” A stranger had asked him, causing Jeongguk to look up, finding the owner of both the voice and the strong smell of boyish cologne. “Hm…?” He hummed, rubbing his eyes lightly. A man with a goofy yet cute smile stood above him, wearing a white shirt, jacket and dark jeans. He had dirty blonde hair which was still rather perfect despite the ovvious fact he had recently been involved with sex (judging by the girl who had just walked out of the room the male had, still struggling to smooth out her skirt). However, there was one thing that Jeongguk couldn’t keep his eyes off ; his dimples. Tiny indents in his cheeks that just made him seem oh so handsome and perfect. It was only then Jeongguk realised that the angel was talking to him yet again, causing him to stutter out an apology.

“I-I’m sorry…I zoned out, what did you say?” He asked, tilting his head causing his rose gold hair to move across his forehead. The man laughed. “No worries bunny. I said I think you’ve had a little too much to drink. You look young, are you sure youre even old enough to be here? You look sixteen. I’m namjoon by the way. Are you here with your older brother or something? Come on, I’m sure we can find him.” ‘Namjoon’ spoke, Jeongguk a little taken back by what he had said. “I’m twenty one, I’m here with my friend.” He began, “Thanks for saying I look young though. Lots of people think that.” Jeongguk stood up, picking up the empty can he had so carelessly left beside him. “I’m just not so used to drinking and got sleepy…I’m Jeongguk.” The younger held out his hand for Namjoon to shake, a little confused when he saw the way his eyes lit up. “You alright?” The shorter male enquires with the raise of a brow, getting a reply of , “Yeah! Sorry, I just don’t get handshakes a lot. I always offer them but they get ignored.”

Unable to resist the urge to giggle, Jeongguk sort of felt sorry for Namjoon, trying to imagine how awkward it must be every time he’s ignored. “That must suck.” He laughed, shoving his hands back into his pockets. The two comintied to talk for a while and ended up laying down on one of the beds in the rooms (after checking for any condoms or cum stains) just to chat and share silly stories to make each other laugh, with different alcoholic beverages that namjoon had provided of course. Due to this, both the boys inevitably ended up completed shit faced, pissing themselves with laughter at things that weren’t even funny. seconds turned into minutes, minutes turned into hours and before ether of them knew it, it was already one am and Jeongguk was being cradled by the taller whom was gently playing with his hair.

“Jeongguk?” A familiar voice could be heard, the younger sitting up only to see Taehyung stood at the door with a worried expression despite the fact he was clearly drunk. “I’ve been calling you for the past twenty minutes, I didn’t know where you were!” He huffed, making his way over to Jeongguk and tugging him off the bed. “Come on, the taxi is here to pick us up.” An audible groan could be heard parting Jeongguk’s lips, causing Namjoon to quickly get up and grab his wrist.

“H-Hey, uh…listen. He can stay for a while longer. I can get him a taxi, he’s fine with me.” Namjoon assured Taehyung who was understandably skeptical at first until Jeongguk looked up at him with a wobbly bottom lip and doe eyes, causing him to huff and let go. “Fine. I want him back by 3am though.” He spoke in a firm voice befor making his way out of the party. The pair were quiet for a minute or so as they stood in the hallway, Namjoon finally breaking the silence.

“Can I have your number?”
